-- Lithwick Joins GMP; Jarvi Leaves Stifel for Paradigm, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-10-11T18:07:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-11/lithwick-joins-gmp-jarvi-leaves-stifel-for-paradigm-vlaad-says.html
 Jeremie Duchesneau Allali moved
from UBS AG to an  investment banking  analyst role at Royal Bank
of Canada, according to Vlaad & Co., a Toronto-based financial
services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  * Toronto-Dominion Bank’s William Ma, an investment-banking
analyst, left for the Bank of Montreal.  * Patrick Ghoche, former investment-banking executive director
at Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce, joined KPMG Corporate
Finance LLC as a managing director.  * Derek Lithwick joined GMP Securities LLC as a vice president
of investment banking from Royal Bank.  * Benjamin Wu was hired as an associate at Borealis from his
previous role as an investment-banking associate in the tech,
media, telecom, power group at  Ontario Teachers’ Pension Plan .  * Former Stifel Financial Corp. renewable energy and clean tech
research associate Mark Jarvi joined Paradigm Capital Inc. in
Toronto covering health care and biotech.  * UBS added Richard Pak in Toronto.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
